Spring MVC does the task of data validation using the validator object which implements the Validator interface. In the custom validator class that we have created, we can use the utility methods of the ValidationUtils class like rejectIfEmptyOrWhitespace() or rejectIfEmpty() to perform validation of the form fields. rejectIfEmptyOrWhitespace() rejectIfEmpty() @Component
public class UserValidator implements Validator
{
   public boolean supports(Class clazz) {
       return UserVO.class.isAssignableFrom(clazz);
   }

   public void validate(Object target, Errors errors)
   {
       ValidationUtils.rejectIfEmptyOrWhitespace(errors, "name", "error.name", "Name is required.");
       ValidationUtils.rejectIfEmptyOrWhitespace(errors, "age", "error.age", "Age is required.");
       ValidationUtils.rejectIfEmptyOrWhitespace(errors, "phone", "error.phone", "Phone is required.");
   }
} @Component
